From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 14:50:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] Fix installer paiDir misnaming + stray ~/.claude/MEMORY/

Upstream issue: danielmiessler/Personal_AI_Infrastructure#1121

The v5.0.0 installer carries v4-era naming where the variable `paiDir`
means Claude home (~/.claude) rather than the PAI data directory
(~/.claude/PAI). The mismatch is acknowledged in the upstream comment
at engine/types.ts:63 (`paiDir: string; // resolved ~/.claude`) and
at engine/config-gen.ts:22-26 ("the variable name `config.paiDir` is
misleading"). The rest of v5.0.0 (hooks/lib/paths.ts) defines
paiDir = ~/.claude/PAI.

22 call sites correctly join "PAI" for PAI-data paths; 5 forgot it.
Plus engine/detect.ts:340 ignores $PAI_DIR despite the adjacent line
reading $PAI_CONFIG_DIR — same pattern, just not applied here.

Manifestations on a fresh install (per #1121):

  1. ~/.claude/MEMORY/{STATE,LEARNING,WORK,RELATIONSHIP,VOICE}/ empty
     skeleton — no hook ever writes there. Real MEMORY is at
     ~/.claude/PAI/MEMORY/.
  2. settings.json counts.signals shipped as 0 because the count probe
     reads ~/.claude/MEMORY/LEARNING (non-existent).
  3. settings.json counts.files shipped as 0 because the count probe
     reads the legacy v2.5–v3.0 path ~/.claude/skills/PAI/USER which
     doesn't exist in v5.0.
  4. UpdateCounts.ts files counter permanently 0 — here paiDir is
     ~/.claude/PAI (inverse semantics) so join(paiDir, 'PAI/USER')
     produces ~/.claude/PAI/PAI/USER (duplicate PAI/ segment).
  5. detect.ts ignores $PAI_DIR — users running PAI from a non-default
     location get the hardcoded ~/.claude.
  6. validate.ts requiredDirs check against the wrong MEMORY paths.
     Currently passes only because manifestation #1 creates the empty
     skeleton at the wrong location. Once #1 is fixed, validate.ts
     must follow.

Files touched (paths relative to upstream source root):

  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PAI-Install/engine/actions.ts            :1244, 1396
  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PAI-Install/engine/detect.ts             :340
  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PAI-Install/engine/validate.ts           :157, 172
  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/handlers/UpdateCounts.ts               :174

Total: 4 files, 6 hunks.

Co-existence note: patch 0005 (validator-spurious-failures) also
touches validate.ts and actions.ts but at different line ranges
(~175 and ~254 in validate.ts; ~1526 in actions.ts). Non-overlapping;
both apply cleanly when 0005 is applied first then 0008.

Hunks generated via `diff -u` against the extracted upstream tarball
(/nix/store/zm296ivyw3qg1a2fm4aa7ns10f3ldy4c-v5.0.0.tar.gz). No
hand-counted @@ headers (lesson from patch 0005 Changelog
2026-05-02T17:35:00Z).
